Node js setup API

installing node.js

creating :
a)index.js file in the main directory
b).env file for sendgrid API key or whatever
c).gitignore {
.env
/node_modules
}

1.Creating package.json file:
npm init --yes

2.Installing dependencies (node_modules appears)
npm i express

sudo npm i -g nodemon

npm i winston

3.For creating the server:
a)In index.js file - const express = require("express")
b)calling the function - const app = express();
c)const port = process.env.PORT || 3900;
const server = app.listen(port,()=> winston.info(`Listening on port ${port}`));
module.exports = server;

